<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1289" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1289">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/32.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consular Agent <persName type="from">Taylor</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Guaymas</hi>
                                </placeName> (<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-12"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date><hi rend="italic">; received December
                                    12, 1913</hi>).</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Additional exorbitant war tax five per cent on business capital imposed
                            by Provisional Governor here payable by December 17, refusal involving
                            penalties. German merchants have wired the German Ambassador,
                            Washington, D. C, claiming exemption according to treaty between Mexico
                            and Germany. American and Chinese merchants, referring to Article III,
                            commercial treaty between the United States and Mexico of 1831, beg your
                            early advice.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Taylor</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>